 the array size must be an integer greater than zero. An array declaration with a zero subscript is legal only for a class, structure, or union member and only with Microsoft extensions ([/Ze](../../build/reference/za-ze-disable-language-extensions.md)).  \n  \n The following sample generates C2466:  \n  \n```  \n// C2466.cpp  \n// compile with: /c  \nint i[0];   // C2466  \nint j[1];   // OK  \nchar *p;  \n```"}